text35.content: 1. Civil Registration and Vital Statistics system: A Civil Registration and Vital Statistics system (CRVS) is an administrative system in a countrythat manages information on births, marriages, deaths and divorces. It generates and stores ‘vital records’ and legal documents such as birthcertificates and death certificates. 📄 You can read more about how deaths are registered around the world in our article: How are causes of deathregistered around the world?
